data.name: Dragonsorb® 3039
data.description: Dragonsorb® 3039 is a liquid UV absorber with a stable morphology. It has good compatibility with all common plasticizers. This product is especially suitable for the stabilizers of PVC-P and PVC plastisol. It can also be used in polyurethane (PUR), polyester, polymethacrylate (PMMA), and other materials to improve the weatherability of the materials under UV conditions.

data.name: Flytac 120 - 90W
data.description: Flytac 120 - 90W is a granular, water-white, modified gum rosin polyols esters made from specially refined gum rosin using a series of advanced processes of partial hydrogenation, esterification, and stabilization. They are a new generation of natural tackifier resins that exhibit good aging resistance, and excellent compatibility. Also capable of raising the initial and persistent viscosity of pressure-sensitive adhesive in a simultaneous way, the excellent heat stability increases by less than 1 degree of Gardner Color within consecutive 8 hours at 180°C.

data.name: Dragonox® PDP
data.description: Dragonox® PDP is a liquid-type antioxidant with good color and heat stability. This product is widely used in polyvinyl chloride (PVC), acrylonitrile butadiene styrene (ABS), polyurethanes (PU), polycarbonates (PC), and coatings.

data.name: Flytac 103 - E

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Glycerol ester of disproportionated rosin, Glycerol ester of wood rosin

data.description:
Flytac 103 - E is a slightly yellow, transparent solid made from gum rosin through esterification with glycerol. This product has a high viscosity, low VOC, excellent heat and aging stability, excellent polymer compatibility, etc.
Typical Uses

EVA, SBS, SIS, and other hot melt adhesives due to their stability and excellent polymer compatibility.
It can also be used in construction adhesives, rubber compounding, sealants, coatings, and other applications.

data.name: Dragonox® 1135
data.description: Dragonox® 1135 is an excellent antioxidant that may be used in a variety of polymers. Because of its low volatility and excellent compatibility, it is particularly well suited for use in forced air cooling processes for PU. This product is used in the stabilization of PV flexible slabstock foams to prevent the formation of peroxides in the polyol during storage and transport and to further protect against scorching during foaming. It also helps prevent fogging in automotive applications, and the low volatility of this product makes it a perfect fit where meat liquids, emulsions, suspensions, solutions, or melts are an integral part of polymer manufacturing and processing. This product has the convenience of a pumpable liquid that can be added before, during, or after polymerization.

data.name: Dragonox® 1315
data.description: Dragonox® 1315 is a low-viscosity liquid-type antioxidant. Due to its alkyl chain, this product has a broad compatibility range and is soluble in various substances. It is an excellent antioxidant for polymers (such as PVC, ABS, etc.), lubricating oil, and polyurethane foam.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 320
data.description: Dragonsorb® 320 is a highly effective light stabilizer that features strong UV absorption, low volatility, and excellent compatibility with a variety of substrates. It protects polymers as well as organic pigments from UV radiation, which helps preserve the original appearance and physical integrity of molded articles, films, sheets, and fibers during outdoor weathering. This product is slightly more discoloring than conventional UV absorbers. It can be used for a variety of plastics and other organic substrates, including unsaturated polyesters, PVC, and PVC plastisol. Additionally, good results are expected when this product is used in polycarbonates, polyurethanes, polyamides, and synthetic fibers, particularly those with a polyester, epoxy, or isocyanate resin base.

data.seo_title: Flyadd - Guangzhou Flying Dragon Chemical Ltd. - Color Developer
data.seo_description: We have a bunch of additive products for various applications. They are Nucleating agents, Optical Brighters, Color developer, Curing, etc.

data.name: Flyadd® KCB
data.description: Flyadd® KCB functions as an optical brightener. This yellowish granule/crystal powder is used as a good whitening agent for plastic films, injection-molded materials, ethylene vinyl acetate (EVA) foamed plastics, and rubber products. It is insoluble in water, but soluble in ordinary organic solvents.

data.name: Flyadd® KSN
data.description: Flyadd® KSN functions as an optical brightener. This yellowish-green crystal powder is used as a good whitening agent for polyester fibers and plastics, polyamide polyacrylonitrile fibers, film, and plastic pressing & injection process. It is insoluble in water, but soluble in ordinary organic solvents.

data.name: Flyadd® 3G
data.description: Flyadd® 3G is a nucleating agent.

data.name: Flyadd® AY1
data.description: Flyadd® AY1 is a color stabilizer and anti-yellowing agent. It is used as a polymer additive for polyurethane and is a highly effective additive for many kinds of dispersed polymer systems. This product has the potential to improve color and heat stability in processing and end applications.

data.name: Flyadd® AY2
data.description: Flyadd® AY2 is a highly efficient liquid-type compounded anti-yellowing agent, which can effectively absorb 240 - 330 nm UV light. It has better resistance to yellowing when compared to the traditional benzophenone type or benzotriazole type UV Absorber. It is widely used in polyurethane foam material for shoes, insoles foam, adhesives for shoes, and other materials. This product is particularly suitable for outdoor use.

data.name: Flyadd® AY3
data.description: Flyadd® AY3 is a liquid-type blend anti-yellowing agent that can inhibit the yellowing of the polyurethane caused by high-temperature processing. It has excellent ultraviolet absorption performance, which can effectively improve the weatherability of the product and inhibit the yellowing caused by thermal oxygen and ultraviolet light.

data.name: Flyadd® AY20
data.description: Flyadd® AY20 is a liquid-type compounded anti-yellowing agent that can increase the thermal resistance and anti-aging properties of PU products. This highly efficient product has excellent anti-thermal oxygen and ultraviolet absorption functions and can effectively inhibit the yellowing caused by high-temperature processing or ultraviolet light.

data.name: Flyadd® AY200
data.description: Flyadd® AY200 is a highly efficient liquid-type compounded anti-yellowing agent. It can increase the thermal resistance and anti-aging properties of EVA products. When compared with traditional additives, the absorption band of this product is wider, which makes it more effective in reducing UV damage to the products. This product can also improve the transparency and long-term stability of the film.

data.name: Flyadd® B1
data.description: Flyadd® B1 is a high-performance β-type nucleator tor polyolefin. It can improve the impact strength and porosity of PP materials. This product is suitable for household appliances, PPR pipes, automobile bumpers, accumulator tanks, batteries, micropore PP fibers, ventilated packaging membranes, lithium battery diaphragms, etc.

data.name: Flyadd® NA11
data.description: Flyadd® NA11 is a highly efficient nucleating agent for polypropylene (PP), polyethylene terephthalate (PET), polybutylene terephthalate (PBT), and polyamide.

data.name: Flyadd® NA21
data.description: Flyadd® NA21 is a highly efficient nucleating and clarifying agent for polypropylene, PET, PBT, and polyamides. It provides excellent transparency and improved mechanical properties such as flexural modulus, crystallization temperatures, HDT, and surface hardness in semi-crystalline polymers. This product also has excellent extraction resistance and no plate-out, exudation, or odor during processing.

data.name: Flyadd® OB
data.description: Flyadd® OB is used for whitening thermoplastic plastics, PVC, PS, PE, PP, ABS, acetate fiber, paint, coating, printing ink, etc. It can be added at any stage during the polymer whitening process to give the finished products a bright bluish-white glaze.

data.name: Flyadd® OB-1
data.description: Flyadd® OB-1 is an optical brightener that is used as a good whitening agent for polyester-cotton blend fabric or various kinds of plastics and their products under high temperatures. This product is insoluble in water, but soluble in high boiling point organic solvents such as phenyl-chloride.

data.name: Flyadd® VA7

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 4-(1,1-Dimethylethyl)phenol polymer with sulfur chloride, Sulfur Chloride Polymer With 4-(1,1-Dimethylethyl)Phenol

data.description: Flyadd® VA7 is a sulfur donor for natural and synthetic rubbers. This product can be used in EV and sime-EV type cure systems as a complete or partial replacement for sulfur, thiuram, and DTDM sulfur donors. It can be used with most typical rubber accelerators and sulfur and is especially good for curing rubber that contains chlorine, such as chlorobutyl and polychloroprene. When used as a partial replacement for sulfur, it tends to improve the dispersion of other additives in the rubber.

data.name: Flyadd® 2-phenylamino-3-methyl-6-dibutylaminofluorane
data.description: Flyadd® 2-phenylamino-3-methyl-6-dibutylaminofluorane is a typical color developer used for thermal and carbonless paper in the paper and pulp industry.

data.name: Flyadd® 2
data.description: Flyadd® 2 is a highly effective clarifier for PP homopolymers and random copolymers.

data.name: Flyadd® 3
data.description: Flyadd® 3 is an efficient nucleating agent for polyolefins. It is used in homopolymer and copolymer polypropylene and LLDPE films, as well as super high molecular weight polyethylene. The results show that the haze is decreased from 37% to about 10% by adding 0.3% Flyadd® 3 in a homopolymer polypropylene injection molded piece of 2mm thickness, and that of polypropylene random copolymer injection molded piece with the same thickness is decreased to about 6%. By adding 0.2% Flyadd® 3, the haze in LLDPE films can be decreased by not less than 87%. It can be employed in the form of a masterbatch, and in conjunction with white oil or other appropriate dispersant agents directly. The recommended processing temperature range of this product is 250 - 270°C.

data.name: Flyadd® 127
data.description: Flyadd® 127 functions as an optical brightener. This light yellow powder is used as a good whitening agent for various kinds of plastics and their products, especially on products of plastics such as polyvinyl chloride (PVC) and polystyrenes (PS).

data.name: Flyadd® 201
data.description: Flyadd® 201 is a non-phenolic color developer used in the production of thermal papers. This white powder is a good alternative for traditional color developers such as Bisphenol A and Bisphenol S.
